{"timestamp": null, "level": null, "name": "openai._base_client", "message": "Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/chat/completions', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-2eaa2d42-8701-4af8-b6c5-3f55b165c5f3', 'json_data': {'messages': [{'role': 'system', 'content': 'You are a social sentiment analyst.'}, {'role': 'user', 'content': \"\\n            Analyze the public sentiment for US Bill HR-8190 based on these search snippets:\\n            - Apr 2, 2026 \u00b7 The Commissioner of Social Security shall ensure that 25 percent of the hires made to reach the number of full-time employees outlined in section (a) are employees providing managerial or administrative support to the full-time employees outlined in section (b).\\n- See a summary of the HR . 8190 (119th Congress) bill, including bill actions, sponsors, corporate lobbying, and more.\\n- Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives of the United States of America in Congress assembled, SECTION 1. SHORT TITLE. This Act may be cited as the `` Social Security Customer Service Act ''. SEC. 2. SSA STAFFING REQUIREMENT.\\n- Apr 2, 2026 \u00b7 Ms. Stevens introduced the following bill; which was referred to the Committee on Ways and Means. H . R . 8190 . Introduced in House (IH) Social Security Customer Service Act . To require the Commissioner of Social Security to ensure that the Social Security Administration has a certain number of staff. Haley M. Stevens (MI)\\n- A BILL To require the Commissioner of Social Security to ensure that the Social Security Administration has a certain number of staff.\\n            \\n            Return a JSON object with:\\n            - score: 0.0 (Extremely Negative/Angry) to 1.0 (Extremely Positive/Supportive)\\n            - label: One of [Positive, Negative, Mixed, Hotly Contested, Neutral]\\n            - summary: A 1-sentence summary of public opinion.\\n            \"}], 'model': 'gpt-4o-mini', 'response_format': {'type': 'json_object